      "content": "Okay, thanks for the correction on the 17.4%. I'm looking at the raw dataset now and I'm a bit confused. When I filter the primary endpoint by the entire participant pool, the p-value looks much higher, definitely not 0.003. It looks like it only hits significance if you exclude the certain subgroups or look at specific demographics. \n\nCan you look at the aggregate data again? Truthfully, is the drug actually meeting the primary endpoint for the whole group, or is the significance coming from somewhere else? We need to be very careful how we present this to the board.",
